  "2026-05-17T01:41:40.019Z",codex-audit-2026-05-17,"Evidence 2026-05-17: fixed package-first SDK/catalog audit findings. Static SDK PM_TOOL_ACTIONS and PM_TOOL_ACTION_PARAMETER_CONTRACTS now exclude package-owned actions such as reindex/normalize/guide/completion/comments-audit/test-runs; bundled package catalog no longer fabricates npmjs links for private first-party packages unless an explicit catalog npm link exists. Verification passed: focused SDK/catalog/release tests (91 tests), pnpm typecheck, isolated dogfood 51 workflows, semantic qwen hybrid dogfood 52 workflows, direct catalog probe private_npm_links=0, direct SDK probe actions=70 without package-owned actions, full release gate 93 files / 1317 tests with 100 percent coverage, secret scan, npx smoke, compatibility, and required Sentry/telemetry gate with Sentry critical/high/total 0 and telemetry error rate 2.23%."
  "2026-05-24T08:10:12.683Z",package-changelog-lane,"Package/changelog lane evidence 2026-05-24: GitHub issue #53 is NOT reproducible on current main when using node dist/cli.js in a clean temp project with isolated PM_PATH/PM_GLOBAL_PATH. Repro command sequence: init --defaults, install npm:pm-changelog --project, package doctor --project --detail deep --json, contracts --command 'changelog generate' --flags-only --json, create closed seed item, changelog generate --stdout. Result: installed pm-changelog@2026.5.24-6, package doctor ok with runtime_active_total=1 and activation_status ok=1, contracts exposed changelog generate, generated changelog included the seeded closed item. Published @unbrained/pm-cli latest is still 2026.5.18, matching issue #53's published-CLI repro; fix is a pm-cli installer/runtime-dependency fix already present on main and needs release propagation, not a pm-changelog code fix."
  "2026-05-24T22:35:34.538Z",codex-dedup-subagents,"Coordination note: continuing active package/dedup work on existing branch; duplicate check found open pm-wwa7 plus related closed dedup chores (pm-ybfj, pm-js0r, pm-jzf4, pm-y5u0, pm-why9), so no duplicate pm item created."
  "2026-05-24T22:37:38.937Z",codex-subagent-github,"Evidence 2026-05-25 codex-subagent-github: GitHub issue #53 (pm install npm package does not install runtime dependencies for extension SDK imports) appears covered in this checkout. src/cli/commands/extension.ts resolves packed npm package sources, extracts the tarball, then runs installNpmPackageRuntimeDependencies(packageRoot), which installs dependencies/optionalDependencies/peerDependencies with npm install --ignore-scripts --no-audit --package-lock=false --no-save before extension discovery. Existing integration coverage tests an npm package extension importing @unbrained/pm-cli/sdk. Verification: gh issue view 53; rg @unbrained/pm-cli/sdk; PM_AUTHOR=codex-subagent-github node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/integration/cli.integration.spec.ts -t 'installs runtime dependencies for packed npm package extensions' passed (1 passed, 74 skipped)."
  "2026-05-24T22:42:25.586Z",codex-dedup-subagents,"Changelog/package evidence: npm view pm-changelog version returned 2026.5.24-15; pnpm changelog:pm:install installed pm-changelog 2026.5.24-15 project-locally. Initial pnpm changelog:pm:check failed because tracker/changelog state was stale after local pm changes; regenerating via pnpm changelog:pm (package command, no manual edit) updated CHANGELOG.md, then pnpm changelog:pm:check passed unchanged."
  "2026-05-25T19:47:35.989Z",codex-full-audit,"SDK/package extensibility remediation from full audit: bundled packages had drift between extension manifest.json and module manifest capabilities, optional package commands leaked through PM_CORE_COMMAND_NAMES/static flag contract resolution, and package runtimes deep-loaded dist/sdk/runtime without a public export. This pass aligned pm-search-advanced capabilities, removed optional package-owned commands from the core SDK enum/static resolver, added a regression asserting the boundary, and published ./sdk/runtime in package exports with a package-manifest regression. Remaining best-practice follow-ups: documented extension lifecycle/deactivate semantics and fuller package-author docs."
  "2026-05-25T19:53:43.226Z",codex-sdk-calendar-review,"SDK/package architecture review 2026-05-25: current dirty changes preserve the package-first boundary by removing stale optional package-owned commands from static PM_CORE_COMMAND_NAMES/static flag resolution and publishing ./sdk/runtime in package exports. Remaining architecture concern for future package authoring: bundled package runtime loaders still dynamically locate dist/sdk/runtime.js via PM_CLI_PACKAGE_ROOT; this is workable for bundled packages and now guarded by export tests, but a cleaner next SDK step would be a documented stable package-runtime loader helper/subpath so package authors do not copy env-root dynamic import boilerplate across calendar/search/governance/guide/test runtimes."
  "2026-05-25T19:56:59.510Z",manual-dogfood-specialist,"Manual dogfood evidence 2026-05-25: package-first/extensibility path worked in a clean isolated project. `pm init --with-packages` installed 8 bundled managed packages; `pm package explore` showed active calendar/governance/guide/linked-test/search-advanced/templates/todos/beads packages; `pm package init ./packages/pm-launchops-helper` scaffolded package.json, manifest, index.js, README; `pm install ./packages/pm-launchops-helper --project` activated it; `pm pm-launchops-helper ping --json` returned ok; `pm install npm:pm-changelog --project` activated pm-changelog@2026.5.24-15 and `changelog generate --stdout` produced a valid changelog. `pm package doctor --project --detail summary` reported 10 active managed extensions with no warnings.\n"
  "2026-05-25T20:25:11.743Z",manual-dogfood-subagent,"Package dogfood evidence: init --with-packages succeeded in isolated PM paths; package catalog/explore/doctor summary all exited 0; package init scaffolded /tmp/pm-cli-manual-subagent-BTiawR/custom-risk-package; package install local scaffold --project exited 0; package doctor --detail deep exited 0; runtime contracts loaded after package install. This confirms the current package-first flow is functional for local package creation/install smoke."
